The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Corporate Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Corporate Briefs
                              
	 Tata Motors global sales have grown 39 per cent in March to 1,01,712 units on robust demand for both commercial and passenger vehicles. The company has also reported an increase of 19 per cent in its global sales during 2009-10 at 8,72,951 units over the previous year. In March, the global sales of luxury brands from Jaguar Land Rover were at 23,538 units, up 43 per cent over the same month last year.                            
	 Essar Oil has posted a profit after tax of Rs 29 crore in 2009-10 against a loss of Rs 514 crore in the previous fiscal. Revenues have increased 1.4 per cent to Rs 42,402 crore from Rs 41,816 crore a year ago. Earnings before interest, taxes, depreciation,           
	d amortisation has grown over 61 per cent to Rs 1,935 crore from Rs 1,203 crore a year ago.                             
	 Castrol India has posted a 29 per cent rise in net sales during the first quarter ended March 2010 at Rs 654 crore compared with Rs 505.9 crore in the year-ago period. Profit after tax has increased 54 per cent to Rs 117.2 crore from Rs 76.3 crore a year ago. Profit before tax increased 55 per cent to Rs 181.8 crore, while net sales were up 29 per cent to Rs 654 crore.                             
	 Arevas transmission and distribution division has won three major turnkey orders from Chhattisgarh State Power Transmission Company and West Bengal State Electricity Transmission Company. Areva will manufacture and install air-insulated substations at the Patan and Vishrampur plants of the Chhattisgarh state utility and the Nazipur plant of the Bengal firm.                             
	 Microsoft has announced the availability of Visual Studio 2010 and .NET Framework 4 in India. These technologies, along with Silverlight 4, will enable developers to target new platforms and build high-quality applications.                             
	 Roots Corporation Ltd, a subsidiary of Indian Hotels Company Ltd  has inaugurated the Ginger Hotel in Surat. The hotel has 98 rooms.                             
	 McNally Bharat Engineering Company has bagged two projects worth Rs 56.64 crore from Hindalco Industries.                                                                                                                                
